Alessandro,

Cantera has not yet been ported to 64 bit machines.  It looks like you  
need to change some compile flags to add -fPIC. But a bigger problem is  
that some work needs to be done to insure that data types are  
consistent.  For example, much of Cantera uses type &quot;doublereal&quot; that  
can be mapped to &quot;double&quot; on 32 bit machines, or to &quot;float&quot; on 64 bit  
machines.  But there are portions that use type &quot;double&quot; explicitly  
(cvode, for example), and these need to be changed to &quot;doublereal&quot;.   
Similar issues arise for type &quot;integer&quot;.

If you want to look at what is needed, check that ext/f2c_libs/f2c.h is  
consistent with the Fortran compiler on your system (if you are linking  
to any Fortran code), and that the definitions there are consistent  
with those in config.h.  Then  try to do a clean build and look for  
error messages about inconsistent data types.

Since I do not have access to a 64 bit machine, I can&#39;t do this  
myself...

Dave Goodwin


